text: The Royal Moroccan Hockey Federation or Fédération Royale Marocaine de Hockey is the governing body of field hockey in Morocco. It is affiliated to IHF International Hockey Federation and AHF African Hockey Federation. The headquarters of the Federation are in Casablanca, Morocco. Kamal Ghallali is President of the Federation. ==History== The federation was established on 15 November 1958. The game was initially practised in Casablanca and was not being developed in the other parts of the country. ==See also== *African Hockey Federation ==References== ==External links== * Morocco-IIHF * Morocco- FIH * Morocco Hockey * Morocco Hockey-FB Morocco Hockey
